<seg id=1> Chinese-Funded Enterprises Become the Largest Foreign Investors in Macao </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Macao, April 3(Xinhua correspondent Wang Zhigeng, Che Yuming)-- At present, there are more than 200 Chinese-funded enterprises in Macao, with a total capital exceeding 90 billion Macao Currency, said Zhang Xuming, President of Macao Chinese Enterprises Association. </seg>
<seg id=3> Chinese-funded enterprises have become the largest foreign investors in Macao. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Zhang Xuming said on the 5th Anniversary of Macao Chinese Enterprises Association the other day that, the mainland-invested enterprises in Macao grew from small to large, weak to strong, and have gradually become an important factor in Macao's economy, </seg>
<seg id=5> contributing a lot to Macao's prosperity and stability. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> As it is introduced, these enterprises made extensive participation in Macao's trade, industry, finance, insurance, tourism, catering, transportation and real estate. </seg>
<seg id=7> Chinese funded business respectively covered 50% of the total volume of finance and insurance, 50% to 70% of tourism, 30% of imports and exports, 70% of real estate. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Zhang Xuming revealed that, the Chinese-funded enterprises in Macao will adhere to Deng Xiaoping's ' One Country, Two System' idea and the central government's general policies towards Hong Kong and Macao, stick to the principle of ' to try to do certain things and refrain from doing other things', and make greater contributions to Macao's economic stability and social development together with the efforts of local businessmen. </seg>
</p>
